00:23:25,040 --> 00:23:28,900
until we find the configuration that minimizes the action,

574
00:23:29,160 --> 00:23:31,390
and that will be the history

575
00:23:31,390 --> 00:23:33,620
of the field in space and time.

576
00:23:34,220 --> 00:23:35,890
That will provide for us

577
00:23:35,890 --> 00:23:37,560
a set of equations of motion.

578
00:23:38,840 --> 00:23:39,440
Okay?

579
00:23:41,700 --> 00:23:42,800
You get the idea,

580
00:23:42,800 --> 00:23:43,960
if not the details?

581
00:23:44,520 --> 00:23:46,360
The details can only be provided

582
00:23:46,360 --> 00:23:48,200
by telling you what the action is.

583
00:23:48,700 --> 00:23:49,900
Just clarification.

584
00:23:49,900 --> 00:23:50,540
So,

585
00:23:50,540 --> 00:23:53,410
the Lagrange formulation still works

586
00:23:53,410 --> 00:23:56,280
if the potential depends on time?

587
00:23:56,500 --> 00:23:56,820
Oh yes,

588
00:23:56,820 --> 00:23:57,100
it does.

589
00:23:57,100 --> 00:23:57,760
Absolutely.

590
00:23:58,160 --> 00:23:58,340
Yeah.

591
00:23:58,480 --> 00:24:00,270
The analog would be something

592
00:24:00,270 --> 00:24:02,060
depending on space and time here.

593
00:24:02,440 --> 00:24:03,000
Yeah.

594
00:24:03,000 --> 00:24:03,660
Yeah.

595
00:24:04,080 --> 00:24:05,160
Lagrangian still works.

596
00:24:05,280 --> 00:24:07,630
What doesn't work if the

597
00:24:07,630 --> 00:24:09,980
Lagrangian depends explicitly on time?

598
00:24:10,360 --> 00:24:11,240
Energy conservation.

599
00:24:11,600 --> 00:24:12,320
Energy conservation.

600
00:24:12,880 --> 00:24:13,200
Right.

601
00:24:14,080 --> 00:24:16,420
But the Lagrangian formulation does work.

602
00:24:16,640 --> 00:24:18,580
So does the Hamiltonian formulation,

603
00:24:18,580 --> 00:24:20,280
it's just that energy is not conserved.

604
00:24:20,580 --> 00:24:21,020
Okay.

605
00:24:21,320 --> 00:24:22,700
And the same thing is true here.

606
00:24:23,940 --> 00:24:24,380
Yeah?

607
00:24:24,720 --> 00:24:26,090
Is the boundary just the bottom

608
00:24:26,090 --> 00:24:27,460
and the top of that rectangle,

609
00:24:27,580 --> 00:24:28,320
or the whole rectangle?

610
00:24:29,680 --> 00:24:30,600
The whole rectangle.

611
00:24:30,880 --> 00:24:32,520
The whole boundary of the rectangle.

612
00:24:32,860 --> 00:24:33,600
All four sides.

613
00:24:33,700 --> 00:24:34,380
All four sides.

614
00:24:35,180 --> 00:24:35,620
Right.

615
00:24:36,160 --> 00:24:37,400
Just as in this case,

616
00:24:37,540 --> 00:24:39,600
we bounded it at the two ends.

617
00:24:41,120 --> 00:24:42,660
We bounded it at the two ends,

618
00:24:42,740 --> 00:24:43,480
here we bound it,

619
00:24:43,960 --> 00:24:47,740
and we hold fixed the value of the field here,

620
00:24:47,740 --> 00:24:49,300
and let it wiggle around.

621
00:24:49,520 --> 00:24:49,660
All right.

622
00:24:49,660 --> 00:24:51,120
So how would we in practice do this?

623
00:24:51,380 --> 00:24:52,420
First of all,

624
00:24:52,420 --> 00:24:55,100
we would need an expression for the action.

625
00:24:56,280 --> 00:24:58,220
The expression for the action will

626
00:24:58,220 --> 00:25:00,160
be just as it is here.

627
00:25:00,360 --> 00:25:02,520
It was an integral over time.

628
00:25:03,060 --> 00:25:04,200
In other words,

629
00:25:04,220 --> 00:25:06,330
a sum of terms for each

630
00:25:06,330 --> 00:25:08,440
one of these little segments here.

631
00:25:09,000 --> 00:25:11,390
We're going to assume that the

632
00:25:11,390 --> 00:25:13,780
action is a sum of terms,

633
00:25:13,820 --> 00:25:16,820
one for each cell,

634
00:25:17,800 --> 00:25:22,440
if we divided this thing up into tiny cells.

635
00:25:23,700 --> 00:25:24,880
In other words,

636
00:25:24,940 --> 00:25:27,340
that it's an integral over space and time.

637
00:25:28,700 --> 00:25:33,400
So we take our region that we're interested in,

638
00:25:36,840 --> 00:25:39,030
we break it up into

639
00:25:39,030 --> 00:25:41,220
a lot of tiny little cells.

640
00:25:45,060 --> 00:25:45,800
This is,

641
00:25:45,800 --> 00:25:46,460
of course,

642
00:25:46,460 --> 00:25:46,800
just a tiny little cell.

643
00:25:46,820 --> 00:25:47,630
And we're going to use this

644
00:25:47,630 --> 00:25:48,440
little trick to implement doing an integral.

645
00:25:49,300 --> 00:25:51,330
An integral over x and t is

646
00:25:51,330 --> 00:25:53,360
just a sum over all these little cells.

647
00:25:53,820 --> 00:25:55,220
And in each cell,

648
00:25:55,420 --> 00:26:00,540
we specify what the action within that cell is,

649
00:26:00,720 --> 00:26:02,300
and then add them all up.

650
00:26:05,000 --> 00:26:07,100
That's the same sort of thing that we did here.

651
00:26:07,300 --> 00:26:09,570
We thought of the action as

652
00:26:09,570 --> 00:26:11,840
a sum over little infinitesimal cells.

653
00:26:12,780 --> 00:26:14,580
So the only other question then,

654
00:26:14,580 --> 00:26:17,400
is what shall we take for the Lagrangian?

655
00:26:18,960 --> 00:26:20,600
So there's a set of rules.

656
00:26:21,360 --> 00:26:24,660
The rules are quite similar and generalize

657
00:26:27,660 --> 00:26:30,940
the mechanics of particles.

658
00:26:32,220 --> 00:26:36,480
It's almost a direct generalization.

659
00:26:38,660 --> 00:26:39,620
First of all,

660
00:26:39,620 --> 00:26:40,340
it should be an integral.

661
00:26:42,260 --> 00:26:44,640
So the action is an integral.

662
00:26:45,760 --> 00:26:48,580
But it's an integral not only over time,

663
00:26:48,740 --> 00:26:50,480
but of space and time.

664
00:26:52,140 --> 00:26:52,700
dx,

665
00:26:52,700 --> 00:26:53,260
dt.

666
00:26:54,420 --> 00:26:55,860
How many dx's?

667
00:26:56,080 --> 00:26:58,640
However many coordinates of space there are.

668
00:26:59,040 --> 00:27:00,900
So we can write this as dx,

669
00:27:00,900 --> 00:27:01,560
let's say,

670
00:27:01,560 --> 00:27:01,800
dy,

671
00:27:01,800 --> 00:27:02,360
dz.

672
00:27:02,720 --> 00:27:04,000
I don't have enough room here.

673
00:27:04,360 --> 00:27:04,860
dx,

674
00:27:04,860 --> 00:27:05,120
dy,

675
00:27:05,120 --> 00:27:05,500
dz.

676
00:27:09,000 --> 00:27:10,180
But in relativity,

677
00:27:10,180 --> 00:27:13,060
we've learned to sort of think of the four coordinates

678
00:27:13,060 --> 00:27:15,080
on a sort of common plane

679
00:27:15,640 --> 00:27:17,680
as being all parts of space-time,

680
00:27:17,940 --> 00:27:20,140
and just give them a name.

681
00:27:21,300 --> 00:27:22,760
All four coordinates,

682
00:27:22,760 --> 00:27:23,600
call them x,

683
00:27:23,600 --> 00:27:23,820
mu,

684
00:27:25,240 --> 00:27:27,240
where mu runs over four values,

685
00:27:27,940 --> 00:27:29,640
time and the three components of space.

686
00:27:30,660 --> 00:27:32,460
And so it's frequently...

687
00:27:37,180 --> 00:27:38,220
It's not just frequently,

688
00:27:38,220 --> 00:27:38,980
it's standard.

689
00:27:40,180 --> 00:27:44,180
To write the integral over all four coordinates of space

690
00:27:44,180 --> 00:27:47,020
as just integral d4x.

691
00:27:48,220 --> 00:27:49,100
Of course,

692
00:27:49,100 --> 00:27:50,460
if we were dealing with a theory

693
00:27:50,460 --> 00:27:52,620
in five or two or one dimension,

694
00:27:52,960 --> 00:27:58,900
we would replace this by d2x,

695
00:27:58,900 --> 00:27:59,560
d4x,

696
00:27:59,560 --> 00:28:00,120
d1x.

697
00:28:01,420 --> 00:28:04,020
What would x be if it was only one dimension?

698
00:28:06,920 --> 00:28:07,640
It would be time.

699
00:28:07,640 --> 00:28:08,540
Right.

700
00:28:08,540 --> 00:28:11,320
So d4x includes dt,

701
00:28:12,040 --> 00:28:14,480
but it also includes the directions of space.

702
00:28:14,740 --> 00:28:15,160
All right,

703
00:28:15,160 --> 00:28:16,740
but you can just think of it as dx,

704
00:28:16,740 --> 00:28:17,040
dy,

705
00:28:17,040 --> 00:28:17,380
dz,

706
00:28:17,380 --> 00:28:17,700
dt.

707
00:28:20,639 --> 00:28:21,120
Then,

708
00:28:21,120 --> 00:28:22,480
some Lagrangian.

709
00:28:25,800 --> 00:28:27,400
Now this Lagrangian is something,

710
00:28:27,400 --> 00:28:27,960
as I said,

711
00:28:28,040 --> 00:28:30,020
which isn't just to be integrated over time,

712
00:28:30,260 --> 00:28:32,500
it's to be integrated over space and time.

713
00:28:32,740 --> 00:28:34,520
It's often called the Lagrange density.

714
00:28:35,280 --> 00:28:37,780
But it's just the analog of Lagrangian here.

715
00:28:37,780 --> 00:28:39,000
And what does it depend on?

716
00:28:39,860 --> 00:28:40,340
Well,

717
00:28:40,340 --> 00:28:41,100
of course,

718
00:28:41,100 --> 00:28:42,560
it's supposed to be a Lagrangian

719
00:28:42,560 --> 00:28:44,900
for the field phi to tell you how phi behaves.

720
00:28:45,480 --> 00:28:47,210
So one of the things it's

721
00:28:47,210 --> 00:28:48,940
certainly going to depend on is phi.

722
00:28:50,860 --> 00:28:53,360
That's the analog of saying the Lagrangian...

723
00:28:53,360 --> 00:28:54,800
We didn't say it over here,

724
00:28:54,920 --> 00:28:57,840
but that's the analog of saying the Lagrangian over here.

725
00:28:57,900 --> 00:28:58,640
It depends on phi.

726
00:28:59,080 --> 00:29:00,300
It depends on position.

727
00:29:01,000 --> 00:29:02,800
It may or may not depend on position,

728
00:29:02,800 --> 00:29:03,360
of course.

729
00:29:03,920 --> 00:29:07,340
But it also depends on the derivatives of phi,

730
00:29:07,780 --> 00:29:10,160
in this case with respect to time.

731
00:29:11,380 --> 00:29:13,350
If time and space are

732
00:29:13,350 --> 00:29:15,320
in the same footing in relativity,

733
00:29:15,740 --> 00:29:18,700
we might expect that the Lagrangian depends

734
00:29:18,700 --> 00:29:22,440
not only on the time derivative of phi,

735
00:29:23,280 --> 00:29:24,440
let's put it in there,

736
00:29:24,440 --> 00:29:26,200
d phi by dt,

737
00:29:29,460 --> 00:29:30,800
but if it's going to

738
00:29:30,800 --> 00:29:32,140
depend on d phi by dt,

739
00:29:32,500 --> 00:29:34,420
and we're dealing in a theory of relativity

740
00:29:34,420 --> 00:29:35,770
where time and space are

741
00:29:35,770 --> 00:29:37,120
in pretty much the same order,

742
00:29:37,780 --> 00:29:38,980
very closely related footing,

743
00:29:39,520 --> 00:29:41,970
we might expect it also

744
00:29:41,970 --> 00:29:44,420
depends on the derivatives of phi

745
00:29:45,679 --> 00:29:47,480
with respect to x,

746
00:29:47,480 --> 00:29:48,500
with respect to y,

747
00:29:48,500 --> 00:29:51,400
with respect to z.

748
00:29:55,060 --> 00:29:57,680
And however many more coordinates there are.

749
00:30:00,040 --> 00:30:01,340
That's the Lagrangian.

750
00:30:01,460 --> 00:30:04,440
The Lagrangian is a function of the field phi.

751
00:30:04,900 --> 00:30:06,420
There may be more than one field,

752
00:30:06,420 --> 00:30:07,120
incidentally.

753
00:30:07,780 --> 00:30:09,720
Just as in this situation over here,

754
00:30:09,960 --> 00:30:12,620
a particle may have more than one coordinate

755
00:30:12,620 --> 00:30:14,020
locating its position.

756
00:30:14,240 --> 00:30:15,120
It might be x,

757
00:30:15,120 --> 00:30:15,320
y,

758
00:30:15,320 --> 00:30:15,500
z,

759
00:30:15,500 --> 00:30:16,120
and so forth.

760
00:30:16,840 --> 00:30:18,480
There may be more than one field,

761
00:30:18,600 --> 00:30:19,320
but for the moment,

762
00:30:19,320 --> 00:30:20,920
let's just concentrate on a problem

763
00:30:20,920 --> 00:30:23,000
with one field called phi.

764
00:30:24,160 --> 00:30:26,340
Then the Lagrangian depends on the field

765
00:30:26,340 --> 00:30:28,300
and its various derivatives.

766
00:30:29,920 --> 00:30:31,900
Doesn't it depend on x,

767
00:30:31,900 --> 00:30:32,160
y,

768
00:30:32,160 --> 00:30:32,460
and z,

769
00:30:32,460 --> 00:30:32,700
too?

770
00:30:32,900 --> 00:30:33,360
It might.

771
00:30:33,820 --> 00:30:37,420
Just as the Lagrangian might depend on t over here.

772
00:30:38,220 --> 00:30:39,040
It might.

773
00:30:41,840 --> 00:30:42,360
Now,

774
00:30:42,360 --> 00:30:44,220
for a closed system,

775
00:30:44,220 --> 00:30:45,500
ordinarily,

776
00:30:45,760 --> 00:30:48,300
a system which has an energy conservation,

777
00:30:48,800 --> 00:30:50,640
it means that the Lagrangian

778
00:30:50,640 --> 00:30:52,480
doesn't depend explicitly on time.

779
00:30:52,820 --> 00:30:54,440
And the same would be true here.

780
00:30:54,640 --> 00:30:57,320
It would not depend explicitly on time or space,

781
00:30:57,320 --> 00:30:57,920
but it could.

782
00:30:58,860 --> 00:31:00,400
Is what we're developing here,

783
00:31:00,400 --> 00:31:02,380
for the case of phi,

784
00:31:02,500 --> 00:31:03,140
a standard field,

785
00:31:03,140 --> 00:31:04,260
or in general?

786
00:31:04,580 --> 00:31:05,340
At the moment,

787
00:31:05,340 --> 00:31:06,540
I haven't...

788
00:31:06,540 --> 00:31:07,200
So far,

789
00:31:07,200 --> 00:31:09,560
I haven't said anything that makes it a scalar field,

790
00:31:10,659 --> 00:31:13,160
other than the fact that I only wrote one component.

791
00:31:14,500 --> 00:31:15,840
If it had been a vector field,

792
00:31:15,840 --> 00:31:17,600
I would have to have some more components.

793
00:31:18,960 --> 00:31:20,980
But if it's a scalar field,

794
00:31:20,980 --> 00:31:22,620
then it would only have one component.

795
00:31:22,780 --> 00:31:23,000
So yes,

796
00:31:23,000 --> 00:31:24,510
I certainly have in the back

797
00:31:24,510 --> 00:31:26,020
of my mind here a scalar field.

798
00:31:26,820 --> 00:31:27,740
But up till now,

799
00:31:27,740 --> 00:31:28,640
it doesn't matter.

800
00:31:28,760 --> 00:31:29,000
I mean,

801
00:31:29,000 --> 00:31:29,620
it could be anything.

802
00:31:31,140 --> 00:31:31,700
All right,

803
00:31:31,700 --> 00:31:34,400
so let's condense notation.

804
00:31:35,659 --> 00:31:40,920
Let's just write this as a function of phi

805
00:31:40,920 --> 00:31:44,900
and the collection of derivatives d phi by dx mu,

806
00:31:45,580 --> 00:31:48,400
of which there are several,

807
00:31:48,500 --> 00:31:51,040
time derivatives and space derivatives.

808
00:31:51,940 --> 00:31:55,000
We could even condense the notation a little bit more.

809
00:31:55,360 --> 00:31:56,500
For time derivative,

810
00:31:56,500 --> 00:31:58,380
we would use phi dot.

811
00:31:59,500 --> 00:32:01,780
What would we use then for space derivatives?

812
00:32:02,760 --> 00:32:03,400
Well,

813
00:32:03,400 --> 00:32:04,380
the nice condition is that

814
00:32:04,400 --> 00:32:06,160
the nice condensed notation is not to use this.

815
00:32:06,260 --> 00:32:11,040
The nice condensed notation is to write phi sub t,

816
00:32:11,040 --> 00:32:13,080
phi sub x,

817
00:32:13,080 --> 00:32:14,180
phi y,

818
00:32:14,180 --> 00:32:15,240
phi z.

819
00:32:15,720 --> 00:32:17,080
And these things mean,

820
00:32:17,080 --> 00:32:18,060
by definition,

821
00:32:18,200 --> 00:32:20,240
the derivative of phi with respect to time,

822
00:32:20,400 --> 00:32:21,680
derivative of phi.

823
00:32:21,820 --> 00:32:24,220
So this would be d phi by dt.

824
00:32:25,320 --> 00:32:27,420
This would be d phi by dx,

825
00:32:27,420 --> 00:32:29,360
and so forth.

826
00:32:30,420 --> 00:32:32,380
That's a more or less standard notation

827
00:32:32,380 --> 00:32:34,950
to put a little t or an

828
00:32:34,950 --> 00:32:37,520
x or a y or z here.

829
00:32:39,680 --> 00:32:40,420
And we could,

830
00:32:40,420 --> 00:32:41,020
if we liked,

831
00:32:41,020 --> 00:32:46,980
write phi sub mu,

832
00:32:47,959 --> 00:32:50,940
meaning the derivative of phi with respect to x mu.

833
00:32:51,260 --> 00:32:52,020
But I won't.

834
00:32:52,040 --> 00:32:53,280
I'm going to leave it the way it is,

835
00:32:53,280 --> 00:32:54,400
d phi by dx mu.

836
00:33:00,000 --> 00:33:01,160
And what's our problem?

837
00:33:01,160 --> 00:33:04,400
Our problem is to solve the problem

838
00:33:04,400 --> 00:33:07,360
of fixing the field on the boundary

839
00:33:09,660 --> 00:33:11,460
and wiggling it around,

840
00:33:12,160 --> 00:33:12,840
you know,

841
00:33:12,840 --> 00:33:13,580
wiggling it around

842
00:33:14,500 --> 00:33:18,040
until we find the configuration that minimizes this action.

843
00:33:19,580 --> 00:33:21,290
If we replace the space and

844
00:33:21,290 --> 00:33:23,000
time by a grid like this,

845
00:33:24,960 --> 00:33:25,980
let's just think about how

846
00:33:25,980 --> 00:33:27,000
we would do it in practice.

847
00:33:27,640 --> 00:33:30,960
We would replace the space-time by the grid of points.

848
00:33:32,160 --> 00:33:34,380
We would replace the Lagrangian.

849
00:33:35,500 --> 00:33:37,760
It would depend on phi at each point.

850
00:33:38,280 --> 00:33:41,380
But what would we replace d phi by dx with?

851
00:33:44,700 --> 00:33:45,740
Little differences.

852
00:33:46,240 --> 00:33:47,280
Little differences.

853
00:33:47,780 --> 00:33:48,420
All right?

854
00:33:48,440 --> 00:33:49,160
And in the process,

855
00:33:49,160 --> 00:33:51,020
we would actually write this action

856
00:33:51,020 --> 00:33:54,040
as a function of the values

857
00:33:54,040 --> 00:33:57,060
of phi at each grid point.

858
00:33:57,540 --> 00:33:58,700
It would just be a function.

859
00:33:58,700 --> 00:34:00,180
It would be a function of a lot of variables.

860
00:34:00,720 --> 00:34:01,840
How many of them?

