01:29:31,840 --> 01:29:32,360
Fields?

2267
01:29:32,700 --> 01:29:33,220
Yeah,

2268
01:29:33,220 --> 01:29:34,880
let's say fields should be continuous.

2269
01:29:35,000 --> 01:29:36,000
If they're not continuous,

2270
01:29:36,000 --> 01:29:37,600
that means they have infinite derivatives.

2271
01:29:37,820 --> 01:29:39,020
And if they have infinite derivatives,

2272
01:29:39,020 --> 01:29:41,100
then they'll have infinite action.

2273
01:29:41,420 --> 01:29:43,220
We haven't spoken about energy yet,

2274
01:29:43,220 --> 01:29:44,460
but they'll have infinite energy.

2275
01:29:45,280 --> 01:29:46,790
Next time we'll come back to

2276
01:29:46,790 --> 01:29:48,300
the energy stored in a field.

2277
01:29:49,280 --> 01:29:53,130
But I wanted to spend another 15 or so

2278
01:29:53,130 --> 01:29:56,980
minutes talking about the relation between particles and fields.

2279
01:29:57,200 --> 01:29:57,720
Now,

2280
01:29:57,720 --> 01:29:59,730
I'm not talking about the quantum

2281
01:29:59,730 --> 01:30:01,740
mechanical relation between particles and fields.

2282
01:30:01,960 --> 01:30:05,500
I'm just talking about the relation between

2283
01:30:05,500 --> 01:30:09,040
ordinary particles and how they interact with fields.

2284
01:30:10,560 --> 01:30:14,620
If I had worked out the rules for

2285
01:30:14,620 --> 01:30:18,680
electrodynamics instead of for a simple scalar field theory,

2286
01:30:19,120 --> 01:30:21,590
I might tell you how charged

2287
01:30:21,590 --> 01:30:24,060
particles interact with an electromagnetic field.

2288
01:30:24,880 --> 01:30:25,960
We haven't done that yet.

2289
01:30:26,000 --> 01:30:26,840
We'll come back to that.

2290
01:30:27,120 --> 01:30:31,190
But let's talk about how a

2291
01:30:31,190 --> 01:30:35,260
particle might interact with a scalar field,

2292
01:30:35,880 --> 01:30:37,540
with this scalar field phi.

2293
01:30:38,420 --> 01:30:40,200
How might it interact with it,

2294
01:30:40,200 --> 01:30:42,480
and how might the presence of the

2295
01:30:42,480 --> 01:30:44,760
scalar field affect the motion of the particle?

2296
01:30:46,200 --> 01:30:47,100
For that,

2297
01:30:47,100 --> 01:30:48,320
we need a Lagrangian.

2298
01:30:49,459 --> 01:30:49,980
And...

2299
01:30:57,200 --> 01:30:58,140
There are many,

2300
01:30:58,140 --> 01:31:00,480
many possible Lagrangians we could

2301
01:31:00,480 --> 01:31:02,820
write down for the same reason.

2302
01:31:03,340 --> 01:31:06,140
Classical mechanics simply doesn't have enough constraints in it to

2303
01:31:06,140 --> 01:31:08,940
tell you in detail what the Lagrangian has to be.

2304
01:31:09,020 --> 01:31:09,680
But we have some rules.

2305
01:31:12,960 --> 01:31:15,980
Let's think about the Lagrangian for a particle.

2306
01:31:15,980 --> 01:31:18,220
Let's say that a particle is moving

2307
01:31:18,220 --> 01:31:20,460
in the presence of a pre-established field.

2308
01:31:21,900 --> 01:31:25,720
Somebody has solved the equations of motion for the field,

2309
01:31:25,720 --> 01:31:28,740
and we know the field phi of x and t.

2310
01:31:29,940 --> 01:31:33,360
It's some specific function of space and time.

2311
01:31:33,700 --> 01:31:36,700
Now a particle is moving in that field.

2312
01:31:37,140 --> 01:31:41,380
That particle might be coupled to the field.

2313
01:31:41,380 --> 01:31:42,990
It might be like a

2314
01:31:42,990 --> 01:31:44,600
charged particle in an electromagnetic field.

2315
01:31:45,420 --> 01:31:46,940
How does the particle move?

2316
01:31:47,560 --> 01:31:48,040
Well,

2317
01:31:48,040 --> 01:31:49,420
to answer that question,

2318
01:31:49,420 --> 01:31:51,480
we ask what kind of Lagrangians...

2319
01:31:51,480 --> 01:31:52,680
I wish this guy would go away.

2320
01:31:52,680 --> 01:31:53,180
Go away.

2321
01:31:54,260 --> 01:31:56,380
West Nile virus coming at you.

2322
01:31:57,140 --> 01:31:57,920
Thank you.

2323
01:32:07,480 --> 01:32:08,260
I'm with you,

2324
01:32:08,260 --> 01:32:08,520
Reese.

2325
01:32:08,700 --> 01:32:09,080
What?

2326
01:32:09,820 --> 01:32:10,300
No,

2327
01:32:10,300 --> 01:32:12,180
I'm a gentle person.

2328
01:32:12,320 --> 01:32:13,660
The race of your mosquito.

2329
01:32:14,140 --> 01:32:14,380
What?

2330
01:32:15,160 --> 01:32:16,020
You think it's a mosquito?

2331
01:32:16,020 --> 01:32:16,980
It doesn't look like a mosquito.

2332
01:32:16,980 --> 01:32:18,060
